The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Onida 

looks beyond TV

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Feb. 19: MIRC Electronics Limited, the owner of the Onida brand, has decided to focus more on growing its non-television business by introducing the latest technological innovations to these products and expects to wrap up this fiscal with a group turnover of Rs 1,500 crore. 

 Around 30 to 35 per cent of its income comes from the non-television segment at present and it is expected to grow to 50 per cent. 

 The company recorded a turnover of Rs 1,200 crore last year on the back of an year-on-year growth of 25 per cent, said Vivek Sharma, vice-president, sales and marketing, MIRC Electronics Limited. 

 Only a 10 per cent of the companys total revenue comes from the eastern region. At present, MIRC Electronics has a market share of 12.5 per cent in digital video disc (DVD) players by volume which is expected to grow by 110 per cent. 




